    "Html": "<p>Hi,</p>\r\n<p>I am using a WPF Toolkit datagrid and I was wondering if it was possible to animate when a row gets clicked (or moused over in my case). &nbsp;Currently, when a row is selected, the rowdetails becomes visible for the respective row, but I would like to make it so that the row details slides out instead of just being displayed immediately. &nbsp;Is this possible?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div id=\"_mcePaste\" style=\"left:-10000px;top:0px;width:1px;height:1px;overflow-x:hidden;overflow-y:hidden\">&lt;tk:DataGrid.RowDetailsTemplate&gt;</div>\r\n<div id=\"_mcePaste\" style=\"left:-10000px;top:0px;width:1px;height:1px;overflow-x:hidden;overflow-y:hidden\">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;DataTemplate&gt;</div>\r\n<div id=\"_mcePaste\" style=\"left:-10000px;top:0px;width:1px;height:1px;overflow-x:hidden;overflow-y:hidden\">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;StackPanel Style=&quot;{StaticResource desc}&quot; Width=&quot;Auto&quot; Orientation=&quot;Horizontal&quot; HorizontalAlignment=&quot;Left&quot;&gt;</div>\r\n<div id=\"_mcePaste\" style=\"left:-10000px;top:0px;width:1px;height:1px;overflow-x:hidden;overflow-y:hidden\">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;StackPanel Style=&quot;{StaticResource descItem}&quot; Orientation=&quot;Horizontal&quot;&gt;</div>\r\n<div id=\"_mcePaste\" style=\"left:-10000px;top:0px;width:1px;height:1px;overflow-x:hidden;overflow-y:hidden\">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;TextBlock Text=&quot;Home Phone: &quot;&gt;&lt;/TextBlock&gt;</div>\r\n<div id=\"_mcePaste\" style=\"left:-10000px;top:0px;width:1px;height:1px;overflow-x:hidden;overflow-y:hidden\">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;TextBlock Text=&quot;{Binding Path=HomeP